(44, 5, 4, 13, 29, 3, 3, 'was it not in thine own power', 'Connection of Generosity and Ownership', 'This connection highlights the theme of personal ownership and the responsibility that comes with it. Both passages emphasize the idea that what one possesses is ultimately under their control and can be dedicated to God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 4, 52, 4, 8, 8, 'thou hast not lied unto men, but unto God', 'Connection of Lying to God', 'Both passages emphasize the seriousness of dishonesty towards God. Acts 5:4 highlights lying to God, while 1 Thessalonians 4:8 indicates that despising God''s commands is equivalent to rejecting Him.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 4, 42, 10, 16, 16, NULL, 'Authority and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability to God. Both passages emphasize that actions taken against God''s representatives are ultimately actions against God Himself.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 4, 2, 35, 21, 22, 'thine own power', 'Willingness in Offerings', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of willingness in giving. Acts 5:4 highlights the internal decision of Ananias, while Exodus 35:21-22 describes those who were stirred in their hearts to bring offerings.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 5, 44, 5, 10, 11, 'great fear came on all them', 'Fear in Response to Death', 'Both passages emphasize the immediate death of Ananias and Sapphira, leading to great fear among the witnesses. This connection highlights the serious consequences of their actions and the impact on the early church.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 5, 44, 2, 43, 43, 'great fear came on all them', 'Fear and Signs in Acts', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of fear among the people in response to divine actions. In Acts 2:43, fear arises from the wonders and signs performed by the apostles, while in Acts 5:5, fear follows the dramatic event of Ananias''s death.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 5, 4, 16, 26, 34, 'great fear came on all them', 'Divine Judgment and Fear', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of divine judgment resulting in fear among the people. In Acts, Ananias''s sudden death instills great fear, similar to how the earth swallowing Korah and his followers caused fear among the Israelites.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 5, 66, 11, 5, 5, 'great fear came on all them', 'Divine Judgment and Fear', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of divine judgment resulting in fear. In Acts, Ananias''s death instills great fear, while in Revelation, the destructive power of the witnesses evokes a similar fear in their enemies.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 5, 66, 11, 13, 13, 'great fear came on all them', 'Fear and Judgment Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of fear and divine judgment. In both passages, a significant event leads to fear among the people, emphasizing the seriousness of God''s actions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 5, 3, 10, 3, 3, 'great fear came on all them', 'Divine Judgment and Fear', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine judgment leading to fear among witnesses. In both passages, the consequences of approaching God improperly result in a profound fear, as seen in Ananias''s death and Aaron''s silence.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 5, 4, 17, 12, 13, 'great fear came on all them', 'Fear of Divine Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the fear that arises from the presence of God''s judgment. In Acts, great fear follows Ananias''s death, while in Numbers, the Israelites express fear of dying near the tabernacle.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 6, 43, 19, 40, 40, 'wound him up', 'Burial Practices in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the act of winding bodies for burial, highlighting a common Jewish burial practice. This connection illustrates the continuity of burial customs in the context of death.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 6, 3, 10, 4, 6, NULL, 'Burial and Mourning Practices', 'Both passages emphasize the act of carrying out the dead, highlighting the importance of proper burial and mourning rituals. In Acts, the young men carry Ananias out to bury him, while in Leviticus, the sons of Uzziel carry their brethren out of the camp.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 6, 5, 21, 23, 23, 'carried him out, and buried him', 'Burial Practices in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the importance of timely burial in both passages. Acts 5:6 describes the immediate burial of Ananias, which parallels Deuteronomy 21:23''s command to bury a body the same day to avoid defilement.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 6, 10, 18, 17, 17, 'carried him out, and buried him', 'Burial Practices in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the act of burial following death. In Acts, the young men carry out a body for burial, while in 2 Samuel, Absalom is cast into a pit and covered with stones, highlighting a common theme of finality in death.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
