(44, 5, 9, 19, 95, 8, 11, 'tempt the Spirit of the Lord', 'Temptation of the Spirit', 'This connection highlights the theme of tempting God. In Acts, Peter addresses Ananias and Sapphira''s deceit as a temptation to the Spirit, paralleling Psalms'' warning against hardening hearts during temptation in the wilderness.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 9, 44, 5, 3, 4, 'tempt the Spirit of the Lord', 'Connection of Lying to God', 'Both passages emphasize the act of lying to the Holy Spirit. Peter confronts Ananias and Sapphira about their deceit, highlighting the seriousness of their actions against God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 9, 19, 78, 56, 56, 'tempt the Spirit of the Lord', 'Tempting the Spirit of God', 'Both passages emphasize the act of tempting God. In Acts, Peter confronts Ananias and Sapphira for testing the Spirit, while Psalms recounts the Israelites provoking the Most High.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 9, 44, 15, 10, 10, 'tempt the Spirit of the Lord', 'Tempting the Spirit of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of testing God, as both passages address the act of tempting the divine. In Acts 5:9, Peter confronts Ananias and Sapphira for testing the Spirit, while in Acts 15:10, the apostles caution against putting a burden on the disciples that God does not desire.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 9, 1, 3, 9, 13, 'tempt the Spirit of the Lord', 'Temptation and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of temptation and accountability in both passages. In Acts, Peter confronts Ananias and Sapphira for their deceit, paralleling God''s inquiry to Adam and Eve about their actions after eating the forbidden fruit.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 9, 2, 17, 2, 2, 'tempt the Spirit of the Lord', 'Tempting the Spirit of the Lord', 'This connection highlights the theme of testing God. Both passages emphasize the act of tempting the Lord, as seen in Peter''s rebuke of Ananias and Sapphira and Moses'' response to the Israelites.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
