(44, 5, 11, 44, 5, 5, 5, 'great fear came upon all', 'Fear in Response to Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of fear that arises in response to divine judgment. In Acts 5:5, Ananias''s death instills fear, which is reiterated in Acts 5:11 as the church and others hear about these events.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
